Step 1 : Create the view
from django.shortcuts import render

def privacy_policy(request):
    return render(request, 'privacy_policy.html')

Step 2 : Create the Template
//templates/privacy_policy.html//
<h2>Privacy Policy</h2>
<p>We value your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we handle your personal information.</p>

<h3>Information We Collect</h3>
<p>We may collect your name, email address, and any messages you send us through the contact form.</p>

<h3>How we Use Information</h3>
<p>Your information is only used to respond to your inquiries. We do not share or sell your data to the third parties. </p>

<h3>Data Security</h3>
<p>We take appropriate measures to keep your data safe.</p>

<h3>Contact Us</h3>
<p>If you have any questions about this policy, please contat us via the contact page.</p>

Step 3 : Create the URL page
//urls.py//
from django.urls import path
from . import views

urlpatterns = [
    path('privacy-policy/', views.privacy_policy, name='privacy_policy'),
]
Step 4 : Add link in the footer
<footer>
   <p>&copy; {{ now.year }}MyWebsite |
        <a href="{% url 'privacy_policy' %}">Privacy Policy</a>
   </p>
</footer> 
